Version 0.65
Release Date: TBA

======================================
Created by
======================================

Ethan Jung (hubbabubbagump)

======================================
Latest update
======================================

Release date:
July 28 2014

Version 0.65
-separated effects upon eating a
 green shroom and red shroom
-green shroom still produces the high
 effect
-red shroom now makes the bear blink
 and has the walls drop while 
 disabling wall collisions; ground
 and ceiling collisions are still 
 in effect however

======================================
Version History
======================================

Version 0.6
-fixed a bug in wall randomization
-fixed hitboxes
-added a button to return to the
 menu on the game over screen
-raised location of ceiling
 (removing it altogether breaks
 the game)
-revamped graphics:
	-changed light background
	-added dark background
	-updated wall graphics
	-created graphics for dirt
	-fixed grass graphics
	-added animations for button 
	 presses

Version 0.5
-changed way versions are handled
-Adding sound effects and BGM
-Added ads
-randomized initial wall positions
-Added a button to view high scores
-updated button graphics
-updated game over screen
-added fruits
-added shrooms
-added score system
-improved wall randomization
-implemented a difficulty increase at 
 50 and 100 points respectively
-added splashscreen and logo

Version 0.4
-Added a scoring system based on a
 velocity / position system
-Added font for numbers and text
-Added gameStates
-Added a way to restart the game
 without closing and reopening the
 game
-added a play button

Version 0.3
-made textures
-added animations
-added sprites
-rendered in objects
-added collision
-added ground and ceiling

Version 0.2
-Initialized a location for the
 bear to start when the game begins
-Retrieves the width and height of
 the device
-Added BearCopter.java which currently
 handles the acceleration and velocity
 of the bear
-implemented velocity limit of 200
-uses a y acceleration value to
 simulate gravity
-Implemented Inputhandler which handles 
input
-returns true when screen is pressed

Version 0.1 
-Created BCGame.java
-Created GameRenderer.java
-Created GameWorld.java
-Created GameScreen.java
-Programmed a rectangle to travel 
left -> right on a black background.
-Created BearCopter.java
-Starting to handle physics of the
 avatar.

